A '''fine on alienation''' (see [[Alienation (property law)]]), in [[feudal law]], was a sum of money paid to the lord by a tenant when he had occasion to make over his land to another.  It is similar in nature to a '''[[Feudal relief|relief]]''', a payment made by an heir to the lord to receive his inheritance.

