Since [[India]] and [[Pakistan]] gained [[Indian independence movement|independence]] in 1947, the [[All-India Muslim League]] and its successor [[Muslim League (Pakistan)|Muslim League]] has seen a steady number of splits and breakaway factions. Some of the breakaway organisations have thrived as [[Independent (politician)|independent]] parties, some have become [[wikt:Defunct|defunct]], while others have merged with the parent party or other political parties. The All-India Muslim League was dissolved in 1947 after the partition. Muslim League (Pakistan) was dissolved in 1958 (by martial law).
